div.p:
A People may be undone by ſome kind of Merchandize;
Ditto. P. 12. 
for many Merchants, ſo they advantage themſelves, care not what Injury they may do to the Publick; for as they were wont formerly, and do ſtill ſerve thoſe of Guiny, to carry them Beads, Looking-Glaſſes, and ſuch like things, and bring away their Gold; ſo they deal often with their own Country-men: For finding us fantaſtical and voluptuous, they tempt us with all ſorts of French Toys, Indy, and Japan Trifles, &c. which fetch away our Money and ſolid Wealth, &c. — But it were well if we could manage the Eaſt-India Trade, as the Dutch do, who carry no Silver from Holland, but drive the Trade with the Silver they get from Japan, in Exchange for other Commodities they bring to them; which we may do in a better, and ſpeedier, way than they can, if permitted by means of the Weſt-Indies, &c.
